          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio on parchment in horizontal format; Qurʾanic text: Q 35:18-31; Sixteen lines per page; At the moment only the image of the fol. 1 verso is given; F1945.19 and another fragment from the same collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/26/verse/225/manuscripts/1274">F1945.20</ref> and two other fragments from the Library of Congress collection <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/27/verse/19/manuscripts/1944">AL-11</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/verse-navigator/sura/6/verse/71/manuscripts/1785">AL-16</ref> originally belonged to the same codex. For a detailed description of sister fragments of these fragments see  the entry by Marcus Fraser: "Doha, Qatar National Library: <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/46/vers/16?handschrift=1418">HC.MS.2017.0010</ref>".  </p>
              <p>Cf. also website of the institution: <ref target="https://asia.si.edu/object/F1945.19/">https://asia.si.edu/object/F1945.19/</ref> </p>
            </summary>
