          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="parchment">
                <support>
                  <p>Fol. 1 recto is flesh side, fol. <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/35/verse/25/manuscripts/1273/page/1v">1 verso</ref> is hair side. </p>
                  <p>Text division: Simple verse separator consists of a group of three strokes arranged one  above the other in the shape of an arrow. Tenth verse separator is  illuminated with gold, red and brown ink. </p>
                </support>
                <extent>Folios: 1
                                    <dimensions unit="mm"><width>195</width><height>257</height></dimensions>
                                </extent>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout writtenLines="16">16 - 16 lines to a page
                                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote/>
            </handDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <summary>
                <p>Script: <hi rend="italic">Kūfī </hi>type B.II. The letter <hi rend="italic">ʾalif</hi> is always vertical, with short return at the baseline in the independent form. The characteristic shape of the letter <hi rend="italic">qāf </hi>in the final position is given with its ending going far to the right. The <hi rend="italic">mašq</hi>-method, the elongation of the horizontal components of the script, is used in the manuscript. Vocalisation is made by red dots. Diacritical marks are used sparsely, originally only the letter <hi rend="italic">nūn </hi>in the independent position is being marked with a dash.  </p>
              </summary>
              <scriptNote>
                                                                kūfī B.II
                            </scriptNote>
            </scriptDesc>
